39
00:02:18,660 --> 00:02:19,480
It's absolutely stunning.

40
00:02:19,620 --> 00:02:20,460
Thank you.

41
00:02:21,590 --> 00:02:24,340
Mrs. He, about this year's
diamonds earning selection,

42
00:02:24,350 --> 00:02:25,990
the results are about to be announced.

43
00:02:25,990 --> 00:02:27,210
If Highland

44
00:02:27,220 --> 00:02:28,580
gets Two Diamonds again this year,

45
00:02:28,580 --> 00:02:29,760
that'll make it four years in a row.

46
00:02:29,760 --> 00:02:30,780
Do you feel

47
00:02:30,780 --> 00:02:31,740
it's already in the bag?

48
00:02:32,530 --> 00:02:34,020
Actually, feeling confident

49
00:02:34,020 --> 00:02:35,260
is more about mindset.

50
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:38,140
Believing brings success.

51
00:02:38,380 --> 00:02:40,580
But for us, it's more than that.

52
00:02:41,340 --> 00:02:43,940
Highland will definitely win again.

53
00:02:44,620 --> 00:02:45,860
That's so bold.

54
00:02:46,100 --> 00:02:47,340
Classic Mrs. He's style.

55
00:02:47,980 --> 00:02:49,020
But I heard

56
00:02:49,020 --> 00:02:50,460
you made a bold statement,

57
00:02:50,460 --> 00:02:51,300
swore an oath,

58
00:02:51,300 --> 00:02:52,860
saying that if Highland

59
00:02:52,860 --> 00:02:53,860
can't earn diamonds,

60
00:02:53,860 --> 00:02:55,020
it'll shut down for good.

61
00:02:55,020 --> 00:02:56,020
Is that actually true?

62
00:03:01,900 --> 00:03:02,740
You know,

63
00:03:02,820 --> 00:03:03,660
a lot of food is made

64
00:03:03,660 --> 00:03:05,740
for people who are hungry.

65
00:03:06,050 --> 00:03:08,300
And some for those who aren't.

66
00:03:09,100 --> 00:03:10,180
But at Highland,

67
00:03:10,420 --> 00:03:12,420
we serve those who appreciate

68
00:03:12,980 --> 00:03:15,380
truly perfect cuisine.

69
00:03:16,290 --> 00:03:17,620
Our dishes

70
00:03:17,640 --> 00:03:20,100
are only for those who get it.

71
00:03:20,330 --> 00:03:22,100
So only a Highland with diamonds

72
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:23,620
deserves to stay open.

73
00:03:24,090 --> 00:03:25,510
I really have no other choice.

74
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:27,140
It shows perfection

75
00:03:27,140 --> 00:03:28,820
is your lifelong pursuit.

76
00:03:29,260 --> 00:03:30,420
Now, from what I know,

77
00:03:31,350 --> 00:03:33,060
you brought your son over from China

78
00:03:33,060 --> 00:03:34,500
a few months ago.

79
00:03:34,580 --> 00:03:36,500
I heard he's always been

80
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:38,060
talented in cooking.

81
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:39,380
Have you ever thought about

82
00:03:39,380 --> 00:03:40,300
letting him

83
00:03:40,300 --> 00:03:42,020
become Highland's head chef?

84
00:03:45,540 --> 00:03:47,380
First, thank you for your kind words.

85
00:03:47,740 --> 00:03:49,420
As his mother,

86
00:03:49,660 --> 00:03:51,380
I know him best.

87
00:03:51,540 --> 00:03:52,940
When Guangyuan was little,

88
00:03:52,940 --> 00:03:54,020
he had a real knack

89
00:03:54,020 --> 00:03:55,620
for making all kinds of food.

90
00:03:55,620 --> 00:03:58,700
But running a restaurant

91
00:03:59,060 --> 00:04:00,620
takes more than just that.

92
00:04:00,620 --> 00:04:01,700
He still needs a lot

93
00:04:01,700 --> 00:04:03,180
of other skills, too.

94
00:04:04,700 --> 00:04:07,180
So I won't let him
be Highland's head chef.

95
00:04:07,180 --> 00:04:08,740
We've communicated

96
00:04:08,740 --> 00:04:10,340
this privately,

97
00:04:10,340 --> 00:04:11,820
and he agreed that.

98
00:04:13,700 --> 00:04:14,860
Now, to answer your question,

99
00:04:14,860 --> 00:04:16,620
why did I bring him over here?

100
00:04:17,540 --> 00:04:19,500
Since I joined Highland,

101
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:21,020
it's been almost seven years

102
00:04:21,020 --> 00:04:22,860
since we last lived together.

103
00:04:22,860 --> 00:04:24,300
I really missed him a lot.

104
00:04:24,340 --> 00:04:25,500
I wanted us to be together

105
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:27,060
and share daily life every day.

106
00:04:27,660 --> 00:04:29,060
That's why I brought him here.

107
00:04:30,340 --> 00:04:31,300
Seven years is honestly

108
00:04:31,300 --> 00:04:32,660
not a short amount of time.

109
00:04:32,660 --> 00:04:34,060
I understand you completely.

110
00:04:35,220 --> 00:04:36,660
Like you said earlier,

111
00:04:36,820 --> 00:04:38,860
managing such a big restaurant

112
00:04:38,860 --> 00:04:39,820
requires someone

113
00:04:39,820 --> 00:04:40,820
with your boldness.

114
00:04:40,820 --> 00:04:42,180
So I've also heard many legends

115
00:04:42,180 --> 00:04:44,340
about you in the industry.

116
00:04:45,960 --> 00:04:46,860
I have another question

117
00:04:46,860 --> 00:04:48,020
I'd like to ask boldly.

118
00:04:48,050 --> 00:04:49,100
Because I heard that a year ago,

119
00:04:49,100 --> 00:04:50,420
you lost your sense of taste,

120
00:04:50,420 --> 00:04:51,800
and now it's gotten worse,

121
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:53,220
requiring part of your tongue
to be removed

122
00:04:53,220 --> 00:04:54,380
to save your life.

123
00:04:54,380 --> 00:04:55,380
Is that true?

124
00:04:55,380 --> 00:04:56,240
Lin.

125
00:04:56,580 --> 00:04:57,420
Okay.

126
00:05:00,860 --> 00:05:01,780
Don't worry about it.

127
00:05:07,700 --> 00:05:08,660
It's okay.

128
00:05:08,660 --> 00:05:10,340
At this moment, I particularly welcome

129
00:05:10,340 --> 00:05:12,140
those who spread rumors

130
00:05:12,380 --> 00:05:13,540
to come to Highland Restaurant

131
00:05:13,540 --> 00:05:14,860
and appreciate our cuisine.

132
00:05:15,220 --> 00:05:16,980
Instead of spreading rumors,

133
00:05:16,980 --> 00:05:18,300
why not just trust

134
00:05:18,300 --> 00:05:19,980
your own taste buds for once?

135
00:05:23,380 --> 00:05:25,100
Alright, thank you.

136
00:05:25,740 --> 00:05:27,100
That's it for today's interview.

137
00:05:28,140 --> 00:05:28,990
Okay.

138
00:05:36,420 --> 00:05:40,180
=Episode 14=

139
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:57,100
Hello, Fabio.

140
00:05:58,260 --> 00:05:59,140
Long time no see.

141
00:05:59,220 --> 00:06:01,020
- Have you been in Italy?
- Yeah.

142
00:06:01,020 --> 00:06:02,660
I've spent the last five years there.

143
00:06:02,660 --> 00:06:04,580
I worked as a farmer for five years.

144
00:06:05,060 --> 00:06:06,860
I lived in Positano the whole time.

145
00:06:06,860 --> 00:06:08,780
Are you really not going
to cook anymore?

146
00:06:08,980 --> 00:06:10,140
I'm still thinking about it.

147
00:06:10,700 --> 00:06:12,140
Highland always welcomes you back.

148
00:06:12,780 --> 00:06:13,660
Attention!

149
00:06:14,610 --> 00:06:15,660
Today's diner, Fabio,

150
00:06:15,660 --> 00:06:17,660
is the chef with the most diamonds
in the world.

151
00:06:17,780 --> 00:06:19,580
He worked at 20 Black Pearl Restaurants.

152
00:06:19,660 --> 00:06:21,620
He used to be
Highland Restaurant's head chef.

153
00:06:21,820 --> 00:06:22,860
Today, he retired five years ago

154
00:06:22,860 --> 00:06:24,120
and has returned to the culinary world.

155
00:06:24,220 --> 00:06:25,820
Do your best. Don't let me down!

156
00:06:25,940 --> 00:06:26,860
Yes, Chef.

157
00:06:27,420 --> 00:06:28,620
So you're planning

158
00:06:29,020 --> 00:06:30,740
to use this current menu

159
00:06:31,140 --> 00:06:33,460
for this year's selection?

160
00:06:33,700 --> 00:06:34,540
Yes.

161
00:06:35,060 --> 00:06:37,220
You know what I mean, right?

162
00:06:38,580 --> 00:06:40,300
The dishes are thoughtful

163
00:06:40,420 --> 00:06:41,340
and warm.

164
00:06:41,860 --> 00:06:43,060
But, He,

165
00:06:43,260 --> 00:06:44,420
don't you think

166
00:06:44,580 --> 00:06:45,900
it gets a bit boring?

167
00:06:45,900 --> 00:06:46,780
We update the menu

168
00:06:46,780 --> 00:06:48,140
every season.

169
00:06:48,140 --> 00:06:49,860
You keep changing menus,

170
00:06:49,980 --> 00:06:52,460
but it's always your mom's vision.

171
00:06:52,540 --> 00:06:54,300
I've worked with her for so long.

172
00:06:54,300 --> 00:06:56,820
Her Highland Restaurant was flawless.

173
00:06:57,340 --> 00:06:58,700
But that was her idea of perfect,

174
00:06:58,700 --> 00:07:00,220
not yours.

175
00:07:11,020 --> 00:07:12,100
Is this trash or what?

176
00:07:13,060 --> 00:07:15,420
Look at all this chocolate.

177
00:07:15,610 --> 00:07:16,460
What even is this?

178
00:07:16,460 --> 00:07:18,460
Fabio's waiting for this dessert.

179
00:07:18,540 --> 00:07:19,460
So clueless!

180
00:07:19,540 --> 00:07:20,540
Why are you still here?

181
00:07:27,740 --> 00:07:30,020
No one's told you to leave yet?

182
00:07:30,980 --> 00:07:31,900
I'd like to see someone try.

183
00:07:32,540 --> 00:07:33,380
Total maniac.

184
00:07:35,220 --> 00:07:36,060
Such a weirdo.

185
00:07:36,580 --> 00:07:38,780
You took my stuff and wear it daily.

186
00:07:40,660 --> 00:07:42,500
If I'm not wrong,

187
00:07:42,540 --> 00:07:44,020
the next dish will be

188
00:07:44,020 --> 00:07:45,740
Armandi chocolate mousse, right?

189
00:07:48,260 --> 00:07:49,140
Fabio.

190
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:50,340
Fine by me.

191
00:07:50,940 --> 00:07:52,900
At least I can taste a memory.

192
00:07:53,220 --> 00:07:55,700
I'm visiting Mrs. He
at the cemetery tomorrow.

193
00:07:56,140 --> 00:07:58,020
Do you want to come along?

194
00:08:01,780 --> 00:08:02,860
Sorry, Fabio.

195
00:08:03,340 --> 00:08:05,500
I've been so busy lately.

196
00:08:13,860 --> 00:08:15,420
Mr. He, there's trouble in the kitchen.

197
00:08:15,420 --> 00:08:16,780
You'd better check it out now.

198
00:08:18,780 --> 00:08:19,640
Fabio,

199
00:08:19,660 --> 00:08:20,900
I'll go check your dessert.

200
00:08:20,910 --> 00:08:21,750
Wait a moment.

201
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:22,600
Alright.

202
00:08:29,940 --> 00:08:30,820
Mr. He is here.

203
00:08:31,260 --> 00:08:32,140
What happened to you?

204
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,460
Chef, what's going on?

205
00:08:50,220 --> 00:08:51,580
I'm here to take back what's mine.

206
00:08:56,900 --> 00:08:57,900
What about the dessert?

207
00:09:00,660 --> 00:09:01,860
I'll give you ten minutes.

208
00:09:02,180 --> 00:09:03,020
Within ten minutes,

209
00:09:03,020 --> 00:09:04,860
Fabio's dessert must be served.

210
00:09:04,860 --> 00:09:05,700
Fabio?

211
00:09:06,100 --> 00:09:07,940
Is Fabio
the Highland's former head chef?

212
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:14,540
You have nine minutes left.

213
00:09:19,660 --> 00:09:20,900
I'm almost done.

214
00:09:21,260 --> 00:09:23,340
Ten minutes. That means starting over.

215
00:09:24,140 --> 00:09:24,980
Curly,

216
00:09:25,620 --> 00:09:26,540
lend me your apron.

217
00:09:26,540 --> 00:09:27,380
Apron?

218
00:09:29,060 --> 00:09:30,260
I need flour and sugar.

219
00:09:30,820 --> 00:09:32,130
The ingredients are in the storage room.

220
00:09:32,340 --> 00:09:33,180
The key is...

221
00:09:34,660 --> 00:09:35,860
Not my problem.

222
00:09:41,620 --> 00:09:44,100
Sis, I can help out.

223
00:09:44,260 --> 00:09:45,180
I'll come with you.

224
00:09:50,460 --> 00:09:51,300
Curly.

225
00:09:51,420 --> 00:09:52,780
- Go get the crusher.
- Got it.

226
00:09:52,780 --> 00:09:54,180
Matsuo, I need some rice.

227
00:09:54,180 --> 00:09:55,660
Do you still have
that vanilla for desserts?

228
00:09:55,660 --> 00:09:57,260
- Any salted lemon left?
- It's inside.

229
00:10:50,140 --> 00:10:51,460
It's really late now.

230
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:52,860
Maybe I should head out first.

231
00:10:53,820 --> 00:10:55,820
Thanks for having me tonight.

232
00:10:59,660 --> 00:11:00,540
Where's Armandi?

233
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:01,500
No idea.

234
00:11:04,580 --> 00:11:05,980
- Fabio.
- No...

235
00:11:05,980 --> 00:11:07,420
Let me try, let me taste it.

236
00:11:18,860 --> 00:11:19,700
Fabio.

237
00:11:20,350 --> 00:11:22,100
Sorry, this must be a mix-up.

238
00:11:22,620 --> 00:11:23,580
Really, I apologize.

239
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:25,580
It's actually a funny coincidence.

240
00:11:25,820 --> 00:11:26,820
Tonight,

241
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:28,020
every single dish

242
00:11:28,020 --> 00:11:29,660
is a copy of Mrs. He's recipes.

243
00:11:30,180 --> 00:11:31,540
But this one stands out.

244
00:11:32,420 --> 00:11:34,500
It feels so full of life,

245
00:11:35,100 --> 00:11:37,180
simple, yet a bit rough.

246
00:11:37,180 --> 00:11:38,620
There's a real passion for cooking.

247
00:11:38,980 --> 00:11:40,580
It reminds me of the first time

248
00:11:40,580 --> 00:11:42,700
I tasted your cheese mousse.

249
00:11:42,860 --> 00:11:43,980
The technique was rough,

250
00:11:43,980 --> 00:11:46,140
but it was special.

251
00:11:46,140 --> 00:11:47,260
I really loved it.

252
00:11:47,660 --> 00:11:48,900
That salty flavor

253
00:11:48,900 --> 00:11:50,380
is totally unexpected.

254
00:11:51,900 --> 00:11:53,500
You should try it yourself.

255
00:12:06,620 --> 00:12:07,580
I'm telling you,

256
00:12:07,580 --> 00:12:09,580
this is the cuisine you should do.

257
00:12:09,900 --> 00:12:10,740
Only by doing this

258
00:12:10,740 --> 00:12:11,900
can you achieve your own perfection

259
00:12:11,900 --> 00:12:13,140
at Highland.

260
00:12:28,660 --> 00:12:29,500
Why is that?

261
00:12:30,780 --> 00:12:32,100
Philip took my things.

262
00:12:32,590 --> 00:12:33,500
I came to take it back.

263
00:12:36,260 --> 00:12:37,180
You could've asked me

264
00:12:37,180 --> 00:12:38,260
for it.

265
00:12:40,460 --> 00:12:41,580
You hit someone.

266
00:12:41,650 --> 00:12:43,180
That can't be forgiven.

267
00:12:43,180 --> 00:12:44,820
And what about what he did?

268
00:12:44,820 --> 00:12:45,940
What did he do

269
00:12:45,940 --> 00:12:47,260
that made you act out?

270
00:12:56,580 --> 00:12:58,220
Last time, when Philip got hurt,

271
00:12:58,220 --> 00:12:59,820
was she involved too?

272
00:13:08,180 --> 00:13:10,060
So you planned it last time as well?

273
00:13:10,940 --> 00:13:11,860
Planned what, exactly?

274
00:13:17,180 --> 00:13:18,260
See for yourself.

275
00:13:35,940 --> 00:13:37,420
Liu Yan, what's so funny?

276
00:13:38,650 --> 00:13:40,620
Philip didn't pursue it last time.

277
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:42,160
But this time, he'll call the police.

278
00:13:42,420 --> 00:13:44,140
Go ahead, call them now!

279
00:13:48,180 --> 00:13:49,220
Philip and his friend

280
00:13:49,220 --> 00:13:50,060
almost...

281
00:13:55,420 --> 00:13:56,860
No surveillance, no evidence.

282
00:13:56,860 --> 00:13:58,180
So no one cares,

283
00:13:58,460 --> 00:13:59,300
Mr. He?

284
00:13:59,900 --> 00:14:01,780
Manager, what did you tell me before?

285
00:14:16,100 --> 00:14:17,060
Everyone, listen up.

286
00:14:25,060 --> 00:14:26,340
Starting today,

287
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:27,900
Philip is no longer

288
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:29,350
the head chef of Highland Restaurant.

289
00:14:36,820 --> 00:14:38,580
- Mr. He...
- You're fired.

290
00:14:41,100 --> 00:14:41,940
Mr. He,

291
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:43,400
is there some mistake here?

292
