00:28:49,500 --> 00:28:52,080
Honestly, Kanta should be the head chef.

584
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:53,100
I'm totally on board with that.

585
00:28:53,100 --> 00:28:54,540
Kanta's got years of experience.

586
00:28:54,540 --> 00:28:55,350
Back when he joined here,

587
00:28:55,440 --> 00:28:56,460
no one even knew who Philip was

588
00:28:56,460 --> 00:28:57,300
or where he was.

589
00:28:57,420 --> 00:28:59,780
Kanta, if you become head chef,

590
00:28:59,780 --> 00:29:01,260
please let me be your assistant.

591
00:29:01,260 --> 00:29:02,100
Is that okay?

592
00:29:02,110 --> 00:29:03,540
Come on, hurry up.

593
00:29:12,340 --> 00:29:13,180
Announcement.

594
00:29:22,620 --> 00:29:24,420
Today is the 982nd day Highland

595
00:29:24,420 --> 00:29:25,700
has lost the diamond rating.

596
00:29:26,540 --> 00:29:27,740
Starting today,

597
00:29:31,220 --> 00:29:32,460
I'll be the head chef

598
00:29:32,620 --> 00:29:33,700
and work together with all of you

599
00:29:34,460 --> 00:29:36,220
to bring Highland back to its prime.

600
00:29:40,140 --> 00:29:42,180
That's awesome!

601
00:30:00,220 --> 00:30:01,100
Morning, Mr. He.

602
00:30:37,180 --> 00:30:38,820
Mr. He,

603
00:30:38,820 --> 00:30:39,980
can I bother you for a second?

604
00:30:40,180 --> 00:30:41,080
Pastry Chef said

605
00:30:41,080 --> 00:30:42,220
that the salted pudding on the menu

606
00:30:42,220 --> 00:30:43,900
has your signature seasoning.

607
00:30:44,500 --> 00:30:45,620
I tried it myself.

608
00:30:46,380 --> 00:30:47,980
The flavor's really unique.

609
00:30:48,140 --> 00:30:50,220
I tried several times at home

610
00:30:50,620 --> 00:30:51,660
to recreate that flavor,

611
00:30:51,660 --> 00:30:53,620
but I couldn't do it.

612
00:30:56,940 --> 00:30:57,820
Besides the original

613
00:30:57,820 --> 00:30:59,100
lemon aroma,

614
00:30:59,580 --> 00:31:01,140
I also noticed

615
00:31:01,300 --> 00:31:02,540
another kind of fruit aroma.

616
00:31:02,700 --> 00:31:04,540
So I tried persimmon, peach,

617
00:31:04,540 --> 00:31:05,380
and apricot.

618
00:31:05,860 --> 00:31:07,220
I think it's probably

619
00:31:07,220 --> 00:31:08,420
processed apricot.

620
00:31:09,380 --> 00:31:10,700
Here's how I handled it.

621
00:31:10,700 --> 00:31:11,820
First, I candied it.

622
00:31:11,820 --> 00:31:13,750
Then I used two kinds of dry spices

623
00:31:13,750 --> 00:31:14,620
to marinate the fruit.

624
00:31:14,620 --> 00:31:15,580
No need to candy them.

625
00:31:17,140 --> 00:31:18,380
Jaya's local apricots

626
00:31:18,700 --> 00:31:20,260
already have rich flavors.

627
00:31:20,260 --> 00:31:22,580
You should learn to pick methods

628
00:31:22,860 --> 00:31:24,260
based on local ingredients.

629
00:31:25,620 --> 00:31:26,940
No need to candy them.

630
00:31:31,940 --> 00:31:32,820
Liu Yan, you certainly

631
00:31:32,820 --> 00:31:34,060
have talent in cooking.

632
00:31:34,220 --> 00:31:35,700
And you use flavor memory well.

633
00:31:36,580 --> 00:31:37,420
But you still can't

634
00:31:37,420 --> 00:31:38,500
become a top chef.

635
00:31:40,900 --> 00:31:42,140
Is there something I'm missing?

636
00:31:42,140 --> 00:31:43,340
I can work harder.

637
00:31:43,780 --> 00:31:45,340
There are two kinds of food.

638
00:31:47,340 --> 00:31:49,060
One is for people who are hungry,

639
00:31:49,900 --> 00:31:51,460
the other is for those who aren't.

640
00:31:52,660 --> 00:31:54,060
Highland makes the second kind.

641
00:31:58,020 --> 00:31:59,860
You want to stay at Highland, right?

642
00:32:02,500 --> 00:32:03,820
First, try to understand Highland.

643
00:32:05,180 --> 00:32:06,340
If you want to understand Highland,

644
00:32:06,340 --> 00:32:08,460
start by thinking about what I said.

645
00:32:11,940 --> 00:32:12,780
Thank you, Mr. He.

646
00:32:27,140 --> 00:32:30,060
(Peach; Asian Pear; Colored Pepper. V;
Crabapple; Beetroot Vinegar)

647
00:32:31,180 --> 00:32:32,020
Miss Liu.

648
00:32:32,780 --> 00:32:33,620
Sorry to bother you.

649
00:32:34,060 --> 00:32:35,660
I'd like to ask you for a favor,

650
00:32:35,660 --> 00:32:36,620
just a personal request.

651
00:32:37,780 --> 00:32:38,620
Go ahead.

652
00:32:38,900 --> 00:32:41,220
Mr. Luo hasn't been well lately.

653
00:32:41,620 --> 00:32:43,020
He can't eat or sleep well.

654
00:32:43,100 --> 00:32:43,940
He keeps telling me

655
00:32:43,940 --> 00:32:45,300
about his past in Beijing.

656
00:32:45,590 --> 00:32:46,460
No wonder.

657
00:32:46,580 --> 00:32:47,740
He hasn't been back in years.

658
00:32:48,140 --> 00:32:50,340
After you cooked for Mr. Luo last time,

659
00:32:50,340 --> 00:32:51,700
he kept talking about it for days.

660
00:32:52,340 --> 00:32:53,460
I want to ask you a favor.

661
00:32:53,740 --> 00:32:55,100
Could you make it for him again?

662
00:32:58,620 --> 00:32:59,460
No problem.

663
00:33:19,500 --> 00:33:20,340
Alright.

664
00:33:24,180 --> 00:33:25,500
Let's put this aside for now.

665
00:33:35,500 --> 00:33:36,540
It smells amazing.

666
00:33:36,940 --> 00:33:37,780
Come on, try it.

667
00:33:44,500 --> 00:33:45,340
I'm...

668
00:33:45,860 --> 00:33:48,180
I'm just a sucker

669
00:33:48,180 --> 00:33:49,460
for noodles.

670
00:33:51,900 --> 00:33:53,180
Luckily, I proofed some dough

671
00:33:53,260 --> 00:33:54,080
in the fridge last night.

672
00:33:55,660 --> 00:33:56,580
Dough proofed overnight

673
00:33:56,580 --> 00:33:57,780
has the best texture.

674
00:34:00,950 --> 00:34:01,820
Noodles without garlic

675
00:34:01,820 --> 00:34:02,820
lose half the joy.

676
00:34:04,540 --> 00:34:05,380
There's garlic too.

677
00:34:08,540 --> 00:34:10,380
The noodles are chewy and tasty.

678
00:34:10,500 --> 00:34:11,460
Of course they are.

679
00:34:12,620 --> 00:34:14,460
How is it in the kitchen

680
00:34:14,460 --> 00:34:15,460
of that luxury hotel?

681
00:34:18,260 --> 00:34:20,260
Honestly, the pressure is intense.

682
00:34:21,900 --> 00:34:23,300
But working together with everyone

683
00:34:23,560 --> 00:34:24,700
and striving to earn diamonds

684
00:34:24,700 --> 00:34:26,100
feels pretty rewarding too.

685
00:34:27,940 --> 00:34:28,980
As long as you're happy.

686
00:34:32,500 --> 00:34:33,500
There's dessert too.

687
00:34:33,700 --> 00:34:34,980
Let me get you some almond tofu.

688
00:34:42,740 --> 00:34:43,780
And here's the sauce.

689
00:34:44,760 --> 00:34:46,740
You could tweak the ratio of white wine.

690
00:34:47,820 --> 00:34:49,860
I want to update the old recipe.

691
00:34:50,140 --> 00:34:52,100
But Mrs. He decided on this recipe.

692
00:34:52,100 --> 00:34:53,460
Is it okay to change it, Chef?

693
00:34:53,460 --> 00:34:54,300
Besides...

694
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:56,220
I want to try a different wine.

695
00:34:59,780 --> 00:35:01,020
How about testing with Huangjiu?

696
00:35:02,060 --> 00:35:03,860
When I was a kid,
my mom made snapper for me.

697
00:35:03,860 --> 00:35:04,900
She used Huangjiu.

698
00:35:09,100 --> 00:35:10,780
Curly, bring me a bottle of Huangjiu.

699
00:35:38,740 --> 00:35:39,820
Adding Huangjiu?

700
00:35:39,820 --> 00:35:40,890
You really think outside the box.

701
00:35:42,700 --> 00:35:43,900
Can I have a taste?

702
00:35:51,100 --> 00:35:52,860
I think adding a bit
to the original sauce

703
00:35:52,860 --> 00:35:53,700
will do.

704
00:35:56,780 --> 00:35:57,620
Curly.

705
00:36:00,460 --> 00:36:01,300
Here you go.

706
00:36:38,020 --> 00:36:39,150
Tastes amazing.

707
00:36:40,340 --> 00:36:42,180
Liu Yan, you're incredible.

708
00:36:45,180 --> 00:36:46,020
So good.

709
00:36:46,090 --> 00:36:46,940
It smells great.

710
00:36:46,940 --> 00:36:48,860
The aroma hits you right away.

711
00:36:50,100 --> 00:36:51,100
You're so good.

712
00:36:51,440 --> 00:36:52,330
A real genius.

713
00:36:53,620 --> 00:36:55,780
(I thought a top chef)

714
00:36:56,020 --> 00:36:58,060
(just needs to make tasty food.)

715
00:36:59,740 --> 00:37:01,020
(Mr. Luo has eaten)

716
00:37:01,020 --> 00:37:02,020
(all kinds of delicious food.)

717
00:37:02,420 --> 00:37:04,580
(Yet a simple bowl
of noodles with savory sauce)

718
00:37:04,580 --> 00:37:05,660
(made him fall asleep.)

719
00:37:09,060 --> 00:37:11,060
(But I think I just
figured something out.)

720
00:37:11,780 --> 00:37:13,940
(The food made by a top chef)

721
00:37:14,650 --> 00:37:16,140
(should have the power to heal.)

722
00:37:23,030 --> 00:37:23,900
Miss,

723
00:37:23,900 --> 00:37:26,060
the person you are looking for
hasn't returned yet.

724
00:37:26,180 --> 00:37:27,940
I promise I'll send you a message

725
00:37:27,940 --> 00:37:29,060
when she comes back.

726
00:37:31,420 --> 00:37:32,260
It's okay.

727
00:37:32,540 --> 00:37:34,100
Is room 403

728
00:37:34,100 --> 00:37:35,340
occupied now?

729
00:37:39,580 --> 00:37:40,470
Thank you.

730
00:38:14,200 --> 00:38:15,240
Don't come out until I call you.

731
00:38:15,240 --> 00:38:16,540
Hurry up!

732
00:38:18,100 --> 00:38:18,940
Be quick, move!

733
00:38:21,680 --> 00:38:23,070
Once I find a job,

734
00:38:23,080 --> 00:38:24,550
I promise I'll pay you all back.

735
00:38:24,550 --> 00:38:26,020
I'm not someone who dodges debt.

736
00:38:27,300 --> 00:38:29,700
You... Go back!

737
00:38:30,140 --> 00:38:31,460
You brat.

738
00:38:38,970 --> 00:38:43,500
♪A silent summer begins to unfold♪

739
00:38:43,760 --> 00:38:48,320
♪Wheat fields stretch beyond my window♪

740
00:38:48,440 --> 00:38:53,070
♪But they've put these shackles on me♪

741
00:38:53,220 --> 00:38:57,170
♪All I can do is imagine that world♪

742
00:38:57,360 --> 00:39:00,520
♪Why can't this stubborn mind
be changed♪

743
00:39:00,520 --> 00:39:03,150
♪Every day,
the end of life keeps changing♪

744
00:39:03,150 --> 00:39:06,930
♪I still long for a free life♪

745
00:39:07,050 --> 00:39:21,470
♪I don't want to stay alone,
waiting for tomorrow♪

746
00:39:21,470 --> 00:39:26,360
♪Come to me, break open these shackles♪

747
00:39:26,360 --> 00:39:31,550
♪Come to me, I'm waiting for you here♪

748
00:39:31,700 --> 00:39:32,860
Stop singing!

749
00:39:33,420 --> 00:39:34,260
Get lost!

750
00:39:52,600 --> 00:39:57,360
♪Mother, I've grown up♪

751
00:39:59,460 --> 00:40:06,400
♪No longer crave my embrace♪

752
00:40:06,880 --> 00:40:13,600
♪No longer need my approval♪

753
00:40:14,290 --> 00:40:20,740
♪No longer afraid
to realize I'm still here♪

754
00:40:21,700 --> 00:40:25,150
♪Countless disappointments;
nothing left to hope for♪

755
00:40:25,390 --> 00:40:29,050
♪We're falling through the air,
endlessly falling down♪

756
00:40:29,050 --> 00:40:32,570
♪There's nothing we can hold on to♪

757
00:40:32,990 --> 00:40:37,290
♪No ground where we can land safely♪

758
00:40:38,740 --> 00:40:40,630
♪(When all hope is gone)♪

759
00:40:40,630 --> 00:40:46,540
♪Our hearts will break
before the dream ends♪

760
00:40:47,280 --> 00:40:51,240
♪We drift along in this dazzling world♪

761
00:40:51,460 --> 00:40:55,410
♪Stumbling through every change
life brings♪

762
00:40:55,410 --> 00:40:58,460
♪The true courage
is simply not looking back♪

763
00:40:59,040 --> 00:41:05,340
♪I finally understand:
The only constant is change♪

764
00:41:06,440 --> 00:41:11,870
♪Mother, I've grown up♪

765
00:41:13,220 --> 00:41:19,920
♪No longer try to fill every void♪

766
00:41:20,740 --> 00:41:27,580
♪No longer saddened by all the goodbyes♪

767
00:41:28,100 --> 00:41:35,070
♪No longer blame; no longer blame♪

768
00:41:35,840 --> 00:41:42,260
♪Mother, I've grown up♪

769
00:41:42,880 --> 00:41:45,980
♪No longer try♪

770
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:50,260
♪To fill every void♪

771
00:41:50,260 --> 00:41:53,870
♪No longer saddened♪

772
00:41:53,900 --> 00:41:57,500
♪By all the goodbyes♪

773
00:41:57,500 --> 00:42:01,140
♪No longer blame♪

774
00:42:01,400 --> 00:42:05,030
♪Love that led nowhere♪
